"{\n    \"Title\": \"Notes to the Consolidated Financial StatementsFor the year ended March 31, 2020\",\n    \"row 1\": \"3. Significant accounting policies (Continued from previous page)\",\n    \"row 2\": \"Cash and cash equivalents\",\n    \"row 3\": \"Cash and cash equivalents include balances with chartered banks and temporary investments with maturities of three\",\n    \"row 4\": \"months or less. Cash subject to restrictions that prevent its use for current purposes is included in restricted cash.\",\n    \"row 5\": \"Marketable securities\",\n    \"row 6\": \"Marketable securities with prices quoted in an active market are measured at fair value while those that are not quoted in an\",\n    \"row 7\": \"active market are measured at cost less impairment.\",\n    \"row 8\": \"Capital assets\",\n    \"row 9\": \"Capital assets are recorded at cost. The cost of major replacements and improvements to capital assets are capitalized and\",\n    \"row 10\": \"the cost of maintenance and repairs are expensed when incurred.\",\n    \"row 11\": \"Amortization is provided using the declining balance and straight-line methods at rates intended to amortize the cost of\",\n    \"row 12\": \"assets over their estimated useful lives.\",\n    \"row 13\": \"Method Rate\",\n    \"row 14\": \"Buildings declining balance 4%\",\n    \"row 15\": \"Automotive declining balance 30 %\",\n    \"row 16\": \"Equipment (computer) straight line 3 years\",\n    \"row 17\": \"Computer software declining balance 100 %\",\n    \"row 18\": \"Equipment (computer and GIS) declining balance 55 %\",\n    \"row 19\": \"Furniture and fixtures declining balance 20 - 30 %\",\n    \"row 20\": \"Leasehold improvements straight-line 5 years\",\n    \"row 21\": \"Parking lot declining balance 8 %\",\n    \"row 22\": \"Website straight-line 3 years\",\n    \"row 23\": \"Solar panels declining balance 30 %\",\n    \"row 24\": \"In the year of acquisition, one-half of the above rates is used on capital assets amortized using the declining balance\",\n    \"row 25\": \"method.\",\n    \"row 26\": \"Leases\",\n    \"row 27\": \"A lease that transfers substantially all of the benefits and risks of ownership is classified as a capital lease. At the inception\",\n    \"row 28\": \"of a capital lease, an asset and a payment obligation are recorded at an amount equal to the lesser of the present value of\",\n    \"row 29\": \"the minimum lease payments and the property\\u2019s fair market value. Assets under capital leases are amortized on a declining\",\n    \"row 30\": \"balance basis, over their estimated useful lives. All other leases are accounted for as operating leases and rental payments\",\n    \"row 31\": \"are expensed as incurred.\",\n    \"row 32\": \"An arrangement contains a lease where the arrangement conveys a right to use the underlying tangible asset, and whereby\",\n    \"row 33\": \"its fulfillment is dependent on the use of the specific tangible asset. After the inception of the arrangement, a reassessment\",\n    \"row 34\": \"of whether the arrangement contains a lease is made only in the event that:\",\n    \"row 35\": \"\\u00b0 there is a change in contractual terms;\",\n    \"row 36\": \"e a renewal option is exercised or an extension is agreed upon by the parties to the arrangement;\",\n    \"row 37\": \"e there is a change in the determination of whether the fulfillment of the arrangement is dependent on the use of the\",\n    \"row 38\": \"specific tangible asset; or\",\n    \"row 39\": \"e there is a substantial physical change to the specified tangible asset.\",\n    \"row 40\": \"Long-lived assets\",\n    \"row 41\": \"Long-lived assets consist of capital assets. Long-lived assets held for use are measured and amortized as described in the\",\n    \"row 42\": \"applicable accounting policies.\",\n    \"row 43\": \"When the Organization determines that a long-lived asset no longer has any long-term service potential to the Organization,\",\n    \"row 44\": \"the excess of its net carrying amount over any residual value is recognized as an expense in the consolidated statement of\",\n    \"row 45\": \"operations. Write-downs are not reversed.\"\n}"